{{wiktionary|εἴσοδος}}

'''Eisodos''' (or eisodoi) is a term used for [[Theatre of Ancient Greece|Ancient Greek Plays]] in order to describe either of two passageways leading into the orchestra, between [[theatron]] and [[Skene (theatre)|skenê]] (also known as the [[parodos]]).

It was used as the exit for the chorus from the orchestra. It has also been called ersodoi.

