'''Icon Theatre''' is a Kent-based UK [[touring theatre]] company producing visual and physical theatre.<ref>{{cite web|title=Edinburgh Festival Fringe Preview : RELEASE|url=http://www.theedinburghreporter.co.uk/2011/07/edinburgh-festival-fringe-preview-release/|work=The Edinburgh Reporter|date=July 31, 2011}}</ref> Icon theatre is run by co-founder Nancy Hirst (artistic) and Sally Armstrong (administrative).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.icontheatre.org.uk/contact.html|title=Icon Theatre: Contact|accessdate=2010-03-20}}</ref>
==Productions== * ''Release'', 2011, about 3 young people newly released from prison,<ref>{{cite web|last=Berkowitz|first=Gerald|title=Release: Pleasance Dome|url=http://ed.thestage.co.uk/reviews/1174|work=The Stage|accessdate=9 October 2012|year=2011}}</ref> winner of a [[Fringe First Award]] at [[Edinburgh Festival Fringe]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Wight|first=Emily|title=www.newstatesman.com/blogs/theatre/2012/06/theatre-review-release|url=http://www.newstatesman.com/blogs/theatre/2012/06/theatre-review-release|accessdate=9 October 2012|date=11 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Fringe 2011 awards roundup|url=http://edinburghfestival.list.co.uk/article/37222-fringe-2011-awards-roundup/|work=The List (Edinburgh & Glasgow)|date=30 August 2011}}</ref> and was awarded five stars by FringeReview<ref>{{cite web|title=Edinburgh Fringe 2011: Release|url=http://www.fringereview.co.uk/fringeReview/4193.html|work=FringeReview|accessdate=9 October 2012}}</ref> * Hard Times, [[Warehouse Theatre]], 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=Review: Hard Times, Warehouse Theatre, Croydon|url=http://www.thisiscroydontoday.co.uk/Review-Hard-Times-Warehouse-Theatre-Croydon/story-11363356-detail/story.html|work=This is Croydon Today|accessdate=9 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Hard Times|url=http://www.thestage.co.uk/reviews/review.php/22265/hard-times|work=The Stage|accessdate=9 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Icon Theatre's adaptation of Hard Times is must-see credit-crunch theatre|url=http://www.croydonguardian.co.uk/search/3817185.Hard_Times__Warehouse_Theatre__Croydon_____/|work=Croydon Guardian|accessdate=9 October 2012}}</ref> * Gradgrind, UK Tour, 2008. * [[The Odyssey]], UK Tour, 2007. * [[The Canterbury Tales]], UK Tour, 2006. * Skeleton Woman, Lady Death, BAC Festival of Visual Theatre, 2004. * The Men's Room, by Joshua James, [[Warehouse Theatre]], 2002.
